BUILDING FROM SOURCE
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
You must install libshout-dev before building ices. Get it from the same place
you found ices, or from www.icecast.org.


For config files, ices depends on libxml2.
Make sure you've got xml-config in your path.

For playlist handlers, ices can optionally use
python or perl.
Add -DWITH_PYTHON and/or -DWITH_PERL flags to the cmake call if you
want this enabled.
For reencoding and streaming non mp3 formats, you'll need libmp3lame-dev, and the -DWITH_LAME=ON flag.

To stream flac files, you'll need libflac-dev, and the -DWITH_FLAC=ON flag.
To stream mp4 files, you'll need libfaad-dev, and the -DWITH_FAAD=ON flag.
To stream vorbis files, you'll need libvorbis-dev, and the -DWITH_VORBIS=ON flag.


to build ices, create output directory: eg.
mkdir build
and let cmake do the rest:

cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
  -DWITH_XML=ON -DWITH_PYTHON=ON -DWITH_PERL=ON -DWITH_LAME=ON \
  -DWITH_VORBIS=ON -DWITH_FAAD=ON -DWITH_FLAC=ON

and then build:
cmake --build build -j

check the result:
build/src/ices -V

Good luck.
